  "body": "Update to include vaccine. Change the values for and where appropriate, adapting our work from and to the SEIR model. In this exercise, we do not address vaccine efficacy or effectiveness, assuming instead a effective vaccine. In the following exercise, number 3 in this section, we include the actual effectiveness of pertussis vaccines.   Compute for pertussis, using the information that for pertussis can be between 5.5 and 17, depending on the outbreak. Your results for will be a range of values.    Adapt the Python code from to run the model with a vaccine level at least as large as . To include vaccine, first include in the code a line for setting the value of , the fraction of people covered by vaccination. Then set S_init=9995*(1-p) and set R_init=9995*p . Adjust the time scale, show just some of the solution curve graphs, or make any other changes needed, to best see the long-term outcome of the model. Write your observations of the outcomes of this model, and compare and contrast with the no-vaccine model.    Do some online research to determine the percentage of children in your area, or percentage of all people in your area, who are vaccinated against pertussis. Your area can refer to your city, state, province, country, or whatever other region you choose. Run the Python code again, using this percentage for vaccination, and citing the resources in which you found the percentage. Adjust the code as needed so you can best see the results, and describe your findings.   "
